content:
5.59. 
Rights of an heir who took possession of the property before the other heirs
1. The heir who has taken possession of the hereditament in the presence of other heirs shall not have the right to dispose of the hereditament (to sell it, mortgage it, etc.) until three months have elapsed from the date on which the succession takes place, or until the heir has obtained a certificate of the right of succession.
2. Before the expiry of the time limit or the receipt of the certificate of succession, the heir shall be entitled to the following only out of the estate:
(1) to pay the costs of the deceased's treatment and care during his illness, as well as the costs of his burial and of the arrangement of his grave;
(2) the maintenance of natural persons who were dependent on the deceased;
3) to ensure the normal functioning of the business (farm);
4. to satisfy claims arising out of the employment relationship;
5) to protect and administer the estate.
